        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 1:44PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 144 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Escalante, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of south central
Garfield County.

This includes Utah Route 12 between mile markers 65 and 78.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
